11:51.912 --> 11:55.013
In many cultures, it's
a father's sacred responsibility

11:55.015 --> 11:56.147
To teach his son to swim,
earl.

11:56.149 --> 11:59.150
Oh. That's all
you gonna come at me with?

11:59.152 --> 12:01.019
You know,
it's a whole lot of stuff

12:01.021 --> 12:06.057
Listen here, girl.
Your daughter can't boil an egg.

12:06.059 --> 12:08.226
Whoa, whoa, whoa!
You don't know what I can do.

12:08.228 --> 12:09.227
Can you?

12:09.229 --> 12:11.062
I-I can --

12:11.064 --> 12:12.864
I can do -- listen.

12:12.866 --> 12:16.167
I can bring dre back to life
if he drowns --

12:16.169 --> 12:18.069
Which he might,
because he can't swim.

12:18.071 --> 12:20.071
Oh, hey, hey, hey,
hey, hey, hey. Look, people.

12:20.073 --> 12:21.906
I'm going nowhere near water,
okay?

12:21.908 --> 12:24.109
Because I<i> don't</i> swim.

12:24.111 --> 12:25.977
Not that I<i> can't.</i>
I<i> don't</i> swim.
See?

12:25.979 --> 12:27.912
Hey, you know what?
Let's not even do this.

12:27.914 --> 12:29.147
Let's not. Actually, dre,
you're totally right.

12:29.149 --> 12:31.082
We are not gonna settle this
tonight, okay?

12:31.084 --> 12:32.951
Our families
are different,

12:32.953 --> 12:35.220
But the point is
that we are<i> family.</i>

12:35.222 --> 12:36.221
That's<i> not</i> the point.

12:36.223 --> 12:39.090
The point is,
they look down on us.

12:39.092 --> 12:41.192
No!
Rainbow:
No, they don't, pops.

12:41.194 --> 12:43.094
Y-yes,<i> she</i> does,
all right?

12:43.096 --> 12:45.063
"not everything
has to be fried"

12:45.065 --> 12:47.899
Is code for
"stop being so black."

12:47.901 --> 12:51.035
It's code
for "stop being so unhealthy."

12:51.037 --> 12:52.103
Ha!
Alicia: Exactly.

12:52.105 --> 12:53.872
You're not obligated
to get diabetes.

12:53.874 --> 12:58.109
And she thinks
we're the<i> bad</i> black.
Preach.

12:58.111 --> 12:59.878
How is that
what you just heard?

12:59.880 --> 13:01.946
That's what I heard.
Dre.

13:01.948 --> 13:04.015
You know, this casserole
is delicious. Very beany.

13:04.017 --> 13:06.251
All my mom is saying
is that there's nothing wrong

13:06.253 --> 13:08.987
With having
an expanded world view.

13:08.989 --> 13:12.090
Of different ways
to experience blackness.

13:12.092 --> 13:16.027
None of which include
the words "rich panoply."

13:16.029 --> 13:17.195
Now you're sounding
like<i> her.</i>

13:17.197 --> 13:18.963
What does that mean?
Huh?

13:18.965 --> 13:22.033
You mean I sound intelligent?
Cultured? Educated?

13:22.035 --> 13:24.035
Pretentious, bougie,
and obnoxious.
No.

13:24.037 --> 13:25.970
Stop. Stop, babe.
[ ruby laughs ]

13:25.972 --> 13:28.006
Here we go.
Come on, y'all.

13:28.008 --> 13:29.974
Here we go!
[ laughs ]

13:29.976 --> 13:31.976
[ chuckling ]
here we go.

13:31.978 --> 13:35.213
<i>That was the most lighthearted</i>
<i>part of dinner.</i>

13:35.215 --> 13:38.883
<i>Once again, they had pulled us</i>
<i>into</i> their<i> drama.</i>

13:38.885 --> 13:42.187
<i>What they thought was a chink</i>
<i>in our marital armor,</i>

13:42.189 --> 13:44.923
<i>They went all-in.</i>

13:44.925 --> 13:47.959
I'm just saying, sometimes
the universe opens a window

13:47.961 --> 13:50.995
So you can climb out
of an unhappy marriage.

13:50.997 --> 13:53.965
You don't have to rush
into anything.

13:53.967 --> 13:56.201
It's just us again.

13:57.970 --> 14:00.171
She's in your taillights,
baby.

14:00.173 --> 14:02.774
[ humming ]

14:06.045 --> 14:07.145
[ groans ]

14:08.113 --> 14:11.916
Babe, you realize
what's happening here, right?

14:11.918 --> 14:13.251
[ sighs ]
our parents are crazy.

14:13.253 --> 14:15.286
Yes,
and it's making<i> us</i> crazy.

14:15.288 --> 14:19.090
I got backed into the world's
first pro-diabetes position.

14:19.092 --> 14:21.025
You made some very valid
arguments, babe.

14:21.027 --> 14:23.161
I was really looking forward
to making this happen.

14:23.163 --> 14:25.129
I've been planning this ceremony
forever,

14:25.131 --> 14:27.031
And I just wanted it
to be perfect.

14:27.033 --> 14:29.000
I ordered birds.

14:29.002 --> 14:31.236
Dre!
I'm terrified of birds.

14:31.238 --> 14:33.238
I even ordered
a convertible hummer limo.

14:33.240 --> 14:35.240
I hate those.
The birds can fly in.

14:35.242 --> 14:37.108
You know,
we can never do anything nice

14:37.110 --> 14:38.243
When our parents
are around.

14:38.245 --> 14:41.012
[ sighs ]
they ruin everything.

14:41.014 --> 14:43.014
I know.

14:44.917 --> 14:46.117
We should go
to the courthouse.

14:46.119 --> 14:47.919
What? No!

14:47.921 --> 14:50.121
I planned some pretty badass
things with orchids.

14:50.123 --> 14:52.924
I know, but when it's just
you and me and the kids,

14:52.926 --> 14:54.225
It's about<i> us</i>
and not about<i> them,</i>

14:54.227 --> 14:56.060
And that's
what's important.

14:56.062 --> 15:00.064
I guess you're right.
All we really need is a judge.

15:00.066 --> 15:01.266
And a big ring.

15:01.268 --> 15:04.035
And 100 white doves.
Mnh-mnh.

15:04.037 --> 15:07.071
Oh. I'll save that
for my next wife.

15:09.975 --> 15:12.343
<i>This</i> is what
they're coming to see.

15:15.047 --> 15:17.015
What you guys doing
all dressed up?

15:17.017 --> 15:21.019
For when we go to the courthouse
with mom and dad.

15:21.021 --> 15:25.223
To...Sit in
on a murder trial...

15:25.225 --> 15:28.259
Of a known
drug kingpin.

15:28.261 --> 15:33.131
José carlos luis
"the jackal" carlos.

15:33.133 --> 15:34.299
Bad man.

15:34.301 --> 15:37.101
And we're definitely
not going to see

15:37.103 --> 15:39.203
Mom and dad get married
tomorrow without you

15:39.205 --> 15:41.940
Because
you guys ruin everything.

15:41.942 --> 15:43.207
Oh.

15:44.944 --> 15:45.944
Yeah, right.

15:45.946 --> 15:47.178
Uh,
you guys look great.

15:47.180 --> 15:49.013
You look
really, really great.

15:49.015 --> 15:50.081
Thank you.

15:50.083 --> 15:51.149
Nailed it!

15:53.018 --> 15:55.186
Are we going to the murder trial
<i>before</i> the wedding?

15:56.121 --> 15:58.289
That'll be a long day.

15:58.291 --> 16:00.224
I should bring a snack.

16:03.162 --> 16:04.295
Is that whole-grain?

16:04.297 --> 16:07.031
No, but it's not fried,
either.

16:07.033 --> 16:09.233
[ sighs ]

16:09.235 --> 16:12.737
Our kids are going to
get married in a courthouse

16:12.739 --> 16:16.074
We have screwed this thing up
for them.

16:18.310 --> 16:20.078
Well...

16:20.080 --> 16:22.180
You more than me.

16:22.182 --> 16:25.016
[ scoffs ]

16:25.018 --> 16:30.188
Your old funk-powered bus
and your rock deodorant.

16:30.190 --> 16:32.256
It's not a rock. It's a crystal.
And it is a natural --

16:32.258 --> 16:34.158
It does not work.

16:34.160 --> 16:35.994
You married a white boy,

16:35.996 --> 16:38.029
And you want your daughter
to marry a white boy.
That's not true.

16:38.031 --> 16:40.164
I wanted a man
that shared my interests,

16:40.166 --> 16:44.002
Who had the courage
to walk mother earth with me.

16:44.004 --> 16:45.269
Oh, negress, please!

16:45.271 --> 16:47.171
You married yourself
a white man,

16:47.173 --> 16:49.774
Splashed on some patchouli,
and reinvented yourself.

16:49.776 --> 16:52.176
You are from memphis,
d'alicia.

16:52.178 --> 16:54.245
Don't be acting like
there's not a glass ceiling

16:54.247 --> 16:56.214
For women
with apostrophes in their name.

16:56.216 --> 17:00.051
The life I built
is better than the life I had.

17:01.754 --> 17:04.055
Okay.

17:04.057 --> 17:06.190
I don't like it,
but I can respect it.

17:06.192 --> 17:08.793
I don't like it that
you walk around with
$11,000 in your pocket.

17:08.795 --> 17:10.061
I don't trust banks.

17:10.063 --> 17:13.131
Well, maybe I'm not,
but you know who<i> is?</i>

17:13.133 --> 17:14.799
My son -- dre, andre.

17:14.801 --> 17:18.136
He eats bulgur
for your daughter.

17:18.138 --> 17:20.171
He would do
pretty much anything for her.

17:20.173 --> 17:22.807
It'd be a shame to see them
get married in a courthouse

17:22.809 --> 17:24.308
'cause we don't know
how to act.

17:26.046 --> 17:28.813
All right. Let me give you
a little taste here.

17:28.815 --> 17:30.281
Oh, not that.
I don't like brown liquor.

17:30.283 --> 17:33.217
I'm eating
white ice cream.

17:33.219 --> 17:35.820
<i>So, in a shocking development,</i>

17:35.822 --> 17:38.756
Our<i> parents</i>
<i>put</i> our<i> wedding back on.</i>

17:38.758 --> 17:41.759
Nobody's gonna be
looking at<i> you,</i> anyway.

17:41.761 --> 17:45.163
<i>And everybody got</i>
<i>what they wanted.</i>

17:45.165 --> 17:47.765
<i>Alicia got</i>
<i>tibetan throat singers.</i>

17:47.767 --> 17:48.800
[ bell dings ]

17:48.802 --> 17:50.268
<i>Moms got her some jesus.</i>

17:50.270 --> 17:52.203
<i>She called bishop don juan.</i>

17:52.205 --> 17:54.272
<i>I called a minister</i>
<i>from</i> this<i> planet.</i>

17:54.274 --> 17:56.274
<i>Pops got a scotch fountain.</i>

17:56.276 --> 17:59.110
<i>And paul got something</i>
<i>he really enjoyed --</i>

17:59.112 --> 18:04.148
<i>To bishop don juan's</i>
<i>dancing double deacons.</i>

18:04.150 --> 18:07.785
<i>And we got what</i> we<i> wanted --</i>
<i>our whole family together.</i>

18:07.787 --> 18:09.821
Now is the time
I have to ask --

18:09.823 --> 18:13.257
Who believes these two
should not be united,

18:13.259 --> 18:14.258
Speak now.

18:14.260 --> 18:16.327
Or forever
hold your peace.

18:16.329 --> 18:18.763
I have something
I would like to say.

18:18.765 --> 18:20.298
Hmm? What?
Oh, mom. Please, no.

18:20.300 --> 18:21.866
Oh, of course you do.

18:21.868 --> 18:23.167
We may never get along.

18:23.169 --> 18:24.268
Preach.

18:24.270 --> 18:25.336
We may never be
best friends.

18:25.338 --> 18:27.205
♪ well ♪

18:27.207 --> 18:29.173
We may never get through
one meal together

18:29.175 --> 18:30.741
Without insulting
one another.

18:30.743 --> 18:32.877
Mama!
Ruby!

18:32.879 --> 18:34.245
But we're family.

18:34.247 --> 18:35.313
Yes.

18:35.315 --> 18:37.315
And the reason
we're family

18:37.317 --> 18:43.754
Is because we are united
in our love for you two.

18:43.756 --> 18:45.289
Aww.

18:45.291 --> 18:46.257
Thank you.
Thanks, mom.

18:46.259 --> 18:47.825
And now dre and bow

18:47.827 --> 18:50.261
Will read the vows
they prepared for each other.

18:50.263 --> 18:51.295
Oh.
Oh.

18:51.297 --> 18:52.797
Huh?
Babe, did you --

18:52.799 --> 18:54.198
You do something?
I didn't do it.

18:54.200 --> 18:55.199
Uh...

18:55.201 --> 18:57.301
Actually, uh,
no offense,

18:57.303 --> 19:00.271
But, uh, you guys have been
such a nightmare that...

19:00.273 --> 19:01.772
Yes. Nightmare.

19:01.774 --> 19:03.274
...We didn't have time
to write any vows.
Mnh-mnh.

19:03.276 --> 19:04.308
No offense taken, son.

19:04.310 --> 19:06.277
Just go ahead.
Speak from your heart.

19:06.279 --> 19:08.279
Nobody's gonna remember
what he says anyway.

19:08.281 --> 19:09.814
[ both chuckle ]

19:09.816 --> 19:13.851
...I promise to love, honor,
and cherish you.

19:13.853 --> 19:16.754
So you just gonna take
all the good ones

19:16.756 --> 19:17.855
Right off the top, huh?
Dre, stop it.

19:17.857 --> 19:22.293
Bow, you believed in me
when no one else did.

19:22.295 --> 19:24.829
And to this day,
I still don't know why

19:24.831 --> 19:27.765
A woman so beautiful who was
almost done with med school

19:27.767 --> 19:30.268
Would bet on me
when she had a far better hand.

19:30.270 --> 19:35.173
But I'm so, so glad
that she did.

19:35.175 --> 19:36.807
Me too.

19:36.809 --> 19:40.344
Oh! Oh! Oh, hey, hey, hey.
No-- uh, n-not right now.

19:40.346 --> 19:41.812
Hold on.
I'm not done yet.

19:41.814 --> 19:43.247
Um...

19:43.249 --> 19:45.216
But I do have one regret.

19:45.218 --> 19:48.252
I wasn't able to get you
the ring that you wanted.

19:48.254 --> 19:51.756
I love the old one, sweetie.
I love it.

19:51.758 --> 19:52.757
Oh, girl. I'm just playing.
[ snaps fingers ]

19:52.759 --> 19:55.259
Oh, thank god.
Oh, thank god.
[ chuckles ]

19:55.261 --> 19:56.294
Bam!

19:56.296 --> 19:58.229
Oh, thank god.
Oh, thank god.

19:58.231 --> 20:00.831
Oh...My god.

20:00.833 --> 20:02.967
By the power vested
in me...
And me.

20:02.969 --> 20:05.236
...I now pronounce you
husband and wife.

20:05.238 --> 20:07.305
Come here.
Kiss your bride!

20:07.307 --> 20:09.307
[ all cheer ]

20:09.309 --> 20:11.309
[ earth, wind & fire's
"September" plays ]

20:11.311 --> 20:13.945
♪ do you remember ♪

20:13.947 --> 20:17.315
♪ the 21st night of September? ♪

20:17.317 --> 20:21.786
♪ love was changing the minds
of pretenders ♪

20:21.788 --> 20:26.290
♪ while chasing the clouds
away ♪

20:26.292 --> 20:27.925
Baby,
throw your bouquet.

20:27.927 --> 20:29.360
♪ ba de ya ♪

20:29.362 --> 20:31.229
♪ say, do you remember? ♪

20:31.231 --> 20:33.231
Give it --
give it to me!
♪ ba de ya ♪

20:33.233 --> 20:34.232
Rainbow: Ruby!

20:34.234 --> 20:35.299
♪ dancing in September ♪

20:35.301 --> 20:36.968
♪ ba de ya ♪

20:36.970 --> 20:38.336
[ laughter ]

20:41.841 --> 20:44.775
You're still married.
What?

20:44.777 --> 20:46.877
I read the small print
on the saturnology website,

20:46.879 --> 20:49.914
And it says all marriages
before 2002 are still valid.

20:49.916 --> 20:51.916
Wait. You mean we were married
this whole time?

20:51.918 --> 20:54.785
Yep. Which means
I'm not a bastard.

20:54.787 --> 20:56.020
Dad is my dad.

20:56.022 --> 20:57.288
We really<i> are</i> twins!

20:57.290 --> 20:59.257
Hold up, friend.

20:59.259 --> 21:01.325
Let's see
what the tests say.

21:01.327 --> 21:03.261
Sorry, zoey.
We can't<i> all</i> be legit.

21:03.263 --> 21:05.296
Well, at least
<i>my</i> dad can hit a jumper.

21:05.298 --> 21:07.798
Hey, enough talk about rick fox,
all right?

21:07.800 --> 21:09.333
Your mother
has never met rick fox.

21:09.335 --> 21:10.401
Right, babe?

21:12.838 --> 21:13.871
Right, babe?

21:13.873 --> 21:15.339
Huh?
Hmm?

21:15.341 --> 21:16.841
Oh.
Wha...

21:16.843 --> 21:18.943
Such a beautiful day out.

21:18.945 --> 21:20.878
Look at the trees.

21:20.880 --> 21:22.947
Oh! Lovely trees.
